Sigli is building the DAWE test harness because we need it to ship our own product. Every financial workflow in Sigli’s neobank, yield allocation, settlement chains, treasury rebalancing, and compliance monitoring, will be verified against the harness before mainnet deployment. The security evidence the harness produces is what we use to satisfy enterprise customers’ procurement and audit requirements.

The grant scope is the open-source test harness and the reference scenarios that make it usable by other teams.

The commercial advantage Sigli is building is in the hosted infrastructure, managed compliance services, and enterprise SLAs that Canton institutions will pay for. Open-sourcing the test harness does not give that away. It establishes Sigli as a Canton contributor and creates the ecosystem adoption of the testing standard that the managed product sits on top of.

Stripe, Twilio, and HashiCorp built durable businesses on the same model: open-source the infrastructure, commercialise the managed layer. The DAWE is Sigli’s infrastructure contribution to Canton. The neobank is the product.

