|---|---|---|---|
| **What it builds** | On-chain financial primitives | Agent identity, MPC wallets, payment stack, settlement | Automated security and QA testing framework for DAML workflows |
| **Sigli’s relationship** | Building on top | Using as infrastructure where applicable | Building and open-sourcing for production use |
| **Who else benefits** | Canton developers broadly | Tenzro ecosystem developers | Any Canton team deploying DAML contracts in an enterprise context |
| **What it unlocks for enterprise** | Necessary foundation | Custody, payments, settlement | Security review evidence, audit documentation, governance sign-off |

## Milestones
The project will be delivered in two phases over 16 weeks.

### Milestone 1 (Weeks 1-6): Test harness on Canton Sandbox
**Deliverables:**
1. Open-source repo with WorkflowScenario.daml (the test harness) and PolicyConfig.daml (the portability adaptor)
2. Reference workflow implementation (WorkflowAgent.daml) as open-source scaffold for other teams to test against
3. Treasury rebalancing scenario test suite, including at least one adversarial scenario, running against the reference workflow on Canton Sandbox
4. Documentation: a single combined guide covering setup, scenario authoring, and security testing

**Acceptance Criteria:**
1. Test harness compiles, deploys, and executes a complete scenario suite on Canton Sandbox
2. Harness covers both correct-path and policy-violation-rejection scenarios, returning structured PASS/FAIL results
3. At least one policy violation scenario correctly triggers on-chain rejection (verified at the contract level, not off-chain assertion)
4. At least one adversarial scenario (unauthorised controller access attempt) fails at the ledger level
5. The combined guide covers all steps from repo clone to test output, with no undocumented prerequisites

### Milestone 2 (Weeks 7-16): Full test suite coverage + Testnet + Mainnet readiness
**Deliverables:**
1. RWA settlement and compliance monitoring scenario test suites, each including at least one adversarial scenario, running against their respective reference workflows on Testnet
2. Regression test runner: re-executes all scenario suites and returns structured output suitable for change-control documentation
3. Testnet deployment with scenarios verified against two registered test party accounts
4. Mainnet readiness guide for teams adopting the harness: infrastructure requirements, HSM key management, and a security review documentation template teams can use with their own auditors
5. Public tutorial covering scenario authoring and security testing

**Acceptance Criteria:**
1. The RWA settlement and compliance monitoring scenario test suites run and pass on Canton Testnet against their reference workflows
2. Regression test runner re-executes all three scenario suites and produces a structured compatibility report
3. RWA settlement scenarios execute successfully against two registered test party accounts on Testnet, both operated by Sigli for this milestone
4. At least one adversarial scenario is included in each of the two new test suites and fails at the ledger level, not in off-chain assertion code
5. The tutorial and documentation cover all steps from scenario authoring to test output, with no undocumented prerequisites
6. Mainnet readiness guide completed and submitted to Canton Foundation for review

